    "summary": "My core research areas are air law and competition regulation of air transport, with a focus on the legal relations and frictions between sovereign States and Non-State actors (airlines, airports, air passengers and shippers of air cargo). I am particularly interested in governance regimes for international aviation, the global economic and environmental challenges that face the sector, and finding innovative legal solutions. \n\nWith over 17 years of experience working in higher education, I am regularly invited to serve as chair and panellist at major aviation and legal conferences, to deliver workshops for government officials and judges, and to provide lectures at institutions around the globe. \n\nIn my previous appointment, I designed and managed City, University of London\u2019s first online degree programme and was awarded The Chancellor\u2019s Award for excellence in teaching and learning. I was Visiting Professor of English Law and Dean of Studies at the Centre for British Studies, Humboldt-Universit\u00e4t zu Berlin, where I since am Honorary Fellow.  \n\nI gained industry knowledge and trade policy expertise from previous appointments at Lufthansa German Airlines and the U.S. Depatment of Commerce, respectively.",
